Whisk together soy sauce, sherry, and sugar in small bowl. Heat oil in wok or large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms and stir-fry 2 minutes. Add shrimp, garlic, and ginger and stir-fry 1 minute. Add spinach and soy mixture and continue stir-frying until spinach has just wilted (shrimp will be cooked), about 1 minute.